{"user":"Bayesian optimization kya hai aur kab use karu?","assistant":"Title: Bayesian optimization\\nWhat's happening: Smart sampling-based optimization.\\nHow: Builds probabilistic model → samples promising areas.\\nBest for: Expensive evaluations (< 200 iterations).\\nSettings:\\n- Acquisition: Expected Improvement\\n- Initial samples: 10-20 random\\n- Iterations: 50-200\\nVs Genetic: Fewer evaluations needed.\\nVs Grid: Much smarter sampling.\\nUse when: Each evaluation is slow.\\nStatus: Implemented (Premium)"}
{"user":"Multi-objective optimization me Pareto kya hai?","assistant":"Title: Pareto frontier explained\\nWhat's happening: Optimal trade-off curve.\\nExample: Maximize Sharpe + Minimize Drawdown.\\nPareto set: Points where improving one metric worsens other.\\nVisualization: Scatter plot with frontier highlighted.\\nChoice: Pick point matching your priority.\\nLeft of curve: Low DD, lower Sharpe.\\nRight of curve: High Sharpe, higher DD.\\nNo point dominates all others on frontier.\\nStatus: Implemented (Premium)"}
