{"user":"EA preset kya hota hai?","assistant":"Title: EA Preset explained\\nWhat's happening: Pre-configured input settings for an EA.\\nPreset contains:\\n- Template file (.tpl) with EA inputs\\n- Name (e.g., Conservative, Aggressive)\\n- Optional: inputs_json for future use\\nHow it works: When Run starts, template is applied to MT5 chart.\\nOne EA can have multiple presets.\\nManage: EA Library → Select EA → Presets tab.\\nStatus: Implemented"}
{"user":"Run kaise start karu headless MT5 pe?","assistant":"Title: Start EA Run on headless MT5\\nWhat's happening: Remote EA execution.\\nNext actions:\\n1) /run-console page.\\n2) Select: MT5 Account, Terminal, EA, Preset.\\n3) Enter: Symbol (EURUSD), Timeframe (H1).\\n4) Set: Slot number, Mode (live/paper).\\n5) Configure: Risk limits (max DD, max lot).\\n6) Click 'Start Run'.\\nFlow: queued → starting → running.\\nMonitor: Status, heartbeats, events, trades.\\nStatus: Implemented"}
{"user":"Run stop kaise karu?","assistant":"Title: Stop EA Run\\nWhat's happening: Gracefully stop running EA.\\nNext actions:\\n1) /run-console → Select active run.\\n2) Click 'Stop' button.\\n3) Flow: running → stopping → stopped.\\n4) Chart closed, EA removed.\\nPanic Stop: Stops ALL runs on terminal immediately.\\nBoth options available in Run Console.\\nStatus: Implemented"}
{"user":"Panic stop kya karta hai?","assistant":"Title: Panic Stop explained\\nWhat's happening: Emergency stop ALL runs.\\nNext actions:\\n1) Run Console → 'Panic Stop' button (red).\\n2) Stops all EAs on selected terminal.\\n3) Optionally closes all open positions.\\n4) Use in emergency situations only.\\nSafety: Immediate effect, no graceful shutdown.\\nStatus: Implemented"}
{"user":"Run status me kya kya states hain?","assistant":"Title: Run State Machine\\nWhat's happening: EA run lifecycle.\\nStates:\\n1) queued: Command created, waiting for Runner\\n2) starting: Runner picked up, applying template\\n3) running: EA active, heartbeats flowing\\n4) stopping: Stop command sent\\n5) stopped: EA removed, chart closed\\n6) error: Something failed\\nAll transitions logged in event timeline.\\nStatus: Implemented"}
{"user":"Runner heartbeat kya hai?","assistant":"Title: Runner Heartbeat\\nWhat's happening: Health monitoring signal.\\nFrequency: Every 5-10 seconds.\\nPayload: CPU%, RAM%, Disk free, MT5 alive, Controller alive, Last tick time.\\nStaleness detection:\\n- < 60s: Online (green)\\n- 60s-5min: Degraded (yellow)\\n- > 5min: Offline (red)\\nCrash loop: > 5 restarts in 10min → auto-disable.\\nStatus: Implemented"}
{"user":"Command queue kaise kaam karta hai?","assistant":"Title: Command Queue Protocol\\nWhat's happening: How MMC talks to Runner.\\nFlow:\\n1) User action → Backend creates runner_commands row (queued)\\n2) Runner polls for queued commands\\n3) Runner acknowledges (acked)\\n4) Runner executes via Controller EA\\n5) Runner reports result (done/error)\\nCommand types: START_RUN, STOP_RUN, RESTART_MT5, APPLY_TEMPLATE, HEALTH_CHECK, PANIC_STOP.\\nStatus: Implemented"}
{"user":"MT5 sync V3 me kya naya hai?","assistant":"Title: MT5 Sync V3 Upgrades\\nWhat's happening: Production-grade sync EA.\\nNew features:\\n1) Exponential backoff + retry (4 retries)\\n2) Circuit breaker (10 fails → 120s cooldown)\\n3) HMAC-SHA256 signature headers\\n4) Delta mode (skip if no changes)\\n5) Watermark persistence (no duplicate deals)\\n6) UTC time handling\\n7) Idempotency keys\\n8) Server-side throttle\\nStatus: Implemented"}
{"user":"MT5 setup wizard kaise use karu?","assistant":"Title: MT5 Setup Wizard\\nWhat's happening: 3-step connection setup.\\nStep 1: Enter Account Number + Broker + Server → Generate Sync Key.\\nStep 2: Copy EA code → Paste in MT5 MetaEditor → Compile (F7) → Attach to chart.\\nStep 3: Click 'Test Connection' → Green checkmark = connected.\\nImportant: Add API URL to MT5 WebRequest allowlist.\\nPath: /mt5-sync\\nStatus: Implemented"}
