{"user":"Prop firm DD mode equity vs balance me kya difference?","assistant":"Title: DD Mode: Equity vs Balance\\nWhat's happening: How drawdown is calculated.\\nEquity-based: DD = (Peak Equity - Current Equity) / Peak Equity\\n- Includes unrealized P&L (open trades)\\n- More strict, real-time monitoring\\nBalance-based: DD = (Peak Balance - Current Balance) / Peak Balance\\n- Only closed trades count\\n- More lenient\\nMost firms use equity-based (safer).\\nSet during challenge creation.\\nStatus: Implemented"}
